    "Following (Ripon and Torresen 2014), the decomposition of these integrated problems requires prior domain knowledge, and the final solution is sensitive to the solution of the previous stage.",
    "Compared to the traditional method, which solves the dynamic optimization problem and the scheduling problem separately, integrated methods can significantly improve the overall performance of the entire process.",
